# Educational Notebook : USCRN Legacy Pairs, GHCNv4 RAW. 
# 8 golden USCRN pairs used
import requests
import tarfile
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import io

# === Settings ===
baseline_start = 1920
baseline_end = 1940
min_months = 11
start_year = 1900
end_year = 2024
smoothing_frac = 0.13

# === Step 1: Download and extract
url = "https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/pub/data/ghcn/v4/ghcnm.tavg.latest.qcu.tar.gz"
response = requests.get(url, stream=True)
tar_bytes = io.BytesIO(response.content)

# Station pairs, the magnificent 8 USCRN (HUSCRN) with more than 90 years data.
pairs = [
    ("USC00012813", "USW00063869"),
    ("USC00294426", "USW00003074"),
    ("USC00402202", "USW00063855"),
    ("USC00250030", "USW00094077"),
    ("USC00018385", "USW00073801"),
    ("USC00380764", "USW00063826"),
    ("USC00013160", "USW00063892"),
    ("USC00348501", "USW00053926")
]
station_ids = {sid for p in pairs for sid in p}

# === Step 2: Extract and grep lines
filtered_lines = []
with tarfile.open(fileobj=tar_bytes, mode="r:gz") as tar:
    dat_member = next(m for m in tar.getmembers() if m.name.endswith(".qcu.dat"))
    dat_file = tar.extractfile(dat_member)
    for line in dat_file:
        sid = line[0:11].decode("utf-8").strip()
        if sid in station_ids and line[15:19].decode("utf-8") == "TAVG":
            filtered_lines.append(line.decode("utf-8"))

# === Step 3: Parse temperature data
records = []
for line in filtered_lines:
    sid = line[0:11].strip()
    year = int(line[11:15])
    if year < start_year or year > end_year:
        continue
    monthly = [int(line[19 + m*8:24 + m*8]) for m in range(12)]
    monthly = [v / 100.0 if v != -9999 else None for v in monthly]
    if sum(v is not None for v in monthly) >= min_months:
        avg = np.mean([v for v in monthly if v is not None])
        records.append([year, avg, sid])

df = pd.DataFrame(records, columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"])

# === Step 4: Build per-pair anomalies (with pairwise baseline subtraction)
pairwise_anomalies = []

for legacy_id, uscrn_id in pairs:
    df_legacy = df[df["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")
    df_uscrn = df[df["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")
    all_years = sorted(set(df_legacy.index).union(df_uscrn.index))
    combined = []
    for y in all_years:
        temps = []
        if y in df_legacy.index:
            temps.append(df_legacy.loc[y, "tavg"])
        if y in df_uscrn.index:
            temps.append(df_uscrn.loc[y, "tavg"])
        if temps:
            combined.append([y, np.mean(temps)])
    df_pair = pd.DataFrame(combined, columns=["year", "tavg"])
    
    # Compute pair-specific baseline
    base = df_pair[(df_pair["year"] >= baseline_start) & (df_pair["year"] <= baseline_end)]
    if not base.empty:
        baseline_mean = base["tavg"].mean()
        df_pair["anomaly"] = df_pair["tavg"] - baseline_mean
        pairwise_anomalies.append(df_pair[["year", "anomaly"]])

# === Step 5: Aggregate anomalies across all pairs (after baseline subtraction)
df_all = pd.concat(pairwise_anomalies)
df_agg = df_all.groupby("year")["anomaly"].mean().reset_index()

# === Step 6: LOESS smoothing
loess = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_agg["anomaly"],
                                exog=df_agg["year"], frac=smoothing_frac)

# === Step 7: Plot (dark background, styled)
plt.style.use('dark_background')
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
ax.plot(df_agg["year"], df_agg["anomaly"], label="Aggregated Anomaly", color='cyan',
        linewidth=2, marker='o', markersize=4, alpha=0.9)
ax.plot(loess[:, 0], loess[:, 1], color='cyan', linewidth=4, alpha=0.6, label="LOESS Trend")

ax.set_title("Historic USCRN Temperature Anomalies (Baseline 1920–1940) – GHCN RAW", fontsize=15, weight='bold')
ax.set_xlabel("Year", fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylabel("Temperature Anomaly (°C)", fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylim(-2, 3)
ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
ax.legend(loc="upper left", fontsize=10)

fig.text(0.01, -0.12,
         "Data Source: GHCN v4.0.1 QCU – NOAA\n"
         "Yearly averages computed from >=11 months per year.\n"
         "Anomalies computed per station pair using 1920–1940 baseline.\n"
         "Then averaged across all 8 pairs.\n",
         fontsize=9, color='white')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import warnings
import io
import sys
import requests
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

import statsmodels.api as sm
import tarfile # Standard library

# Attempt to import Basemap

    from mpl_toolkits.basemap import Basemap
    basemap_available = True
    print("Basemap library found.")
except ImportError:
    print("Warning: Basemap library not found. Map inlay will be skipped.")
    basemap_available = False


# Suppress specific warnings if needed (optional)
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=UserWarning, module='statsmodels')
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=RuntimeWarning) # For mean of empty slice
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=FutureWarning)
# Suppress Basemap deprecation warning if present

# === Settings ===
baseline_start = 2010
baseline_end = 2015
min_months = 10
start_year = 1910 # User changed this
end_year = 2024
smoothing_frac = 0.13
country_filter_prefix = "US"

# Metadata URL and filtering criteria
metadata_url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/orwell2024/GHCN-tools/main/GHCNv4_stations_with_BI_BU_orwell2022.csv"
bu_column_name = "Built_2020_10km_percent"
meta_station_id_col = "ID"
meta_lat_col = "Lat"
meta_lon_col = "Lon"

# Criteria for the LOW BU filtered series
low_bu_min = 0.1
low_bu_max = 2.0

# Criteria for the HIGH BU filtered series
high_bu_min = 10.0 # Stations > 10%

# GHCNv4 data URL
ghcn_data_url = "https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/pub/data/ghcn/v4/ghcnm.tavg.latest.qcu.tar.gz"

# Station pairs for the "H8 USCRN" series
original_pairs = [
    ("USC00012813", "USW00063869"), ("USC00294426", "USW00003074"),
    ("USC00402202", "USW00063855"), ("USC00250030", "USW00094077"),
    ("USC00018385", "USW00073801"), ("USC00380764", "USW00063826"),
    ("USC00013160", "USW00063892"), ("USC00348501", "USW00053926")
]
original_station_ids = {sid for p in original_pairs for sid in p}

# --- Step 0: Load Metadata and Filter Stations ---
df_meta_us_indexed = None
low_bu_station_ids = set(); high_bu_station_ids = set()
all_needed_ids = set(original_station_ids)
print("--- Step 0: Load Metadata and Filter Stations ---")
try:
    meta_response = requests.get(metadata_url); meta_response.raise_for_status()
    df_meta = pd.read_csv(io.StringIO(meta_response.text), sep=',', engine='python')
    required_meta_cols = [meta_station_id_col, bu_column_name, meta_lat_col, meta_lon_col]
    if not all(col in df_meta.columns for col in required_meta_cols): raise ValueError(f"Metadata missing required columns: {[c for c in required_meta_cols if c not in df_meta.columns]}")
    df_meta[meta_station_id_col] = df_meta[meta_station_id_col].astype(str)
    df_meta_us = df_meta[df_meta[meta_station_id_col].str.startswith(country_filter_prefix, na=False)].copy()
    df_meta_us[bu_column_name] = pd.to_numeric(df_meta_us[bu_column_name], errors='coerce')
    df_meta_us[meta_lat_col] = pd.to_numeric(df_meta_us[meta_lat_col], errors='coerce')
    df_meta_us[meta_lon_col] = pd.to_numeric(df_meta_us[meta_lon_col], errors='coerce')
    df_meta_us = df_meta_us.dropna(subset=[bu_column_name, meta_station_id_col, meta_lat_col, meta_lon_col])
    df_meta_us_indexed = df_meta_us.set_index(meta_station_id_col) # Store indexed version for map lookup
    low_bu_meta = df_meta_us[ (df_meta_us[bu_column_name] >= low_bu_min) & (df_meta_us[bu_column_name] <= low_bu_max) ]
    low_bu_station_ids = set(low_bu_meta[meta_station_id_col].unique())
    high_bu_meta = df_meta_us[ df_meta_us[bu_column_name] > high_bu_min ]
    high_bu_station_ids = set(high_bu_meta[meta_station_id_col].unique())
    all_needed_ids.update(low_bu_station_ids); all_needed_ids.update(high_bu_station_ids)
    print(f"Metadata processed: Low BU stations={len(low_bu_station_ids)}, High BU stations={len(high_bu_station_ids)}, Total unique stations={len(all_needed_ids)}")
except Exception as e: print(f"Metadata Error: {e}"); sys.exit("Exiting due to metadata failure.")

# --- Steps 1-3: Download, Extract, Parse GHCN Data ---
# (No changes needed here)
print("\n--- Step 1 & 2: Download, Extract, Grep GHCNv4 data ---")
filtered_lines = []; dat_member_name = "Unknown"
try:
    response = requests.get(ghcn_data_url, stream=True); response.raise_for_status(); tar_bytes = io.BytesIO(response.content)
    with tarfile.open(fileobj=tar_bytes, mode="r:gz") as tar:
        dat_members = [m for m in tar.getmembers() if m.name.endswith(".qcu.dat")]; dat_member = dat_members[0]; dat_member_name = dat_member.name
        print(f"Extracting from: {dat_member_name}"); dat_file = tar.extractfile(dat_member);
        for line_bytes in dat_file:
             try: line_str = line_bytes.decode("utf-8", errors='replace'); sid = line_str[0:11].strip();
             except Exception : continue
             if sid in all_needed_ids and line_str[15:19] == "TAVG": filtered_lines.append(line_str)
except Exception as e: print(f"Tar Error: {e}"); sys.exit()
print(f"Found {len(filtered_lines)} TAVG lines.")

print("\n--- Step 3: Parse temperature data ---")
records = []
for line in filtered_lines:
    try:
        sid = line[0:11].strip(); year = int(line[11:15])
        if year < start_year or year > end_year: continue
        monthly_temps = []; valid_months = 0
        for m in range(12):
            val_str = line[19 + m*8 : 24 + m*8].strip()
            if val_str and val_str != "-9999": temp = int(val_str) / 100.0; monthly_temps.append(temp); valid_months += 1
            else: monthly_temps.append(None)
        if valid_months >= min_months: yearly_avg = np.nanmean([v for v in monthly_temps if v is not None]);
        if not np.isnan(yearly_avg): records.append([year, yearly_avg, sid])
    except Exception as e: print(f"Parsing Warning: {e}")
df_raw = pd.DataFrame(records, columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"])
print(f"Parsed {len(df_raw)} valid yearly averages (min_months={min_months}, start_year={start_year}).")

# --- Data Processing & Anomaly Calculation ---
h8_stations_used_final = list(original_station_ids) # Keep all original IDs for map
low_bu_stations_used_final = []; high_bu_stations_used_final = [] # Store actual IDs used
df_agg_original = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly']); df_agg_low_bu = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly']); df_agg_high_bu = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly'])
final_low_bu_station_count = 0; final_high_bu_station_count = 0

# --- Series 1: H8 USCRN ---
print(f"\n--- Step 4a/5a: H8 USCRN Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_start}-{baseline_end}) ---")
original_pairwise_anomalies = []; df_raw_original = df_raw[df_raw['station_id'].isin(original_station_ids)]
if not df_raw_original.empty:
    h8_pairs_with_baseline = 0
    for legacy_id, uscrn_id in original_pairs:
        df_legacy = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]; df_uscrn = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
        df_pair_tavg = pd.concat([df_legacy, df_uscrn], axis=1).mean(axis=1).reset_index(); df_pair_tavg.columns = ["year", "tavg"]
        base_vals = df_pair_tavg[(df_pair_tavg["year"] >= baseline_start) & (df_pair_tavg["year"] <= baseline_end)]["tavg"]
        if not base_vals.empty and base_vals.notna().any(): baseline_mean = base_vals.mean(); df_pair_tavg["anomaly"] = df_pair_tavg["tavg"] - baseline_mean; original_pairwise_anomalies.append(df_pair_tavg[["year", "anomaly"]]); h8_pairs_with_baseline += 1
    if original_pairwise_anomalies: df_all_original = pd.concat(original_pairwise_anomalies); df_agg_original = df_all_original.groupby("year")["anomaly"].mean().reset_index(); print(f"Aggregated H8 USCRN from {h8_pairs_with_baseline} pairs.")
    else: print("Error: No H8 USCRN pairs had baseline data.")
else: print("Error: No data for H8 stations.")

# --- Series 2: LOW BU US Stations ---
print(f"\n--- Step 4b/5b/6b: LOW BU US Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_start}-{baseline_end}) ---")
df_raw_low_bu = df_raw[df_raw['station_id'].isin(low_bu_station_ids)]
low_bu_stations_meeting_criteria = []
if not df_raw_low_bu.empty:
    grouped = df_raw_low_bu.groupby('station_id'); total_years_required = end_year - start_year + 1
    for station_id, group in grouped:
        if (group['year'].nunique() == total_years_required and group['year'].min() == start_year and group['year'].max() == end_year): low_bu_stations_meeting_criteria.append(station_id)

            df_agg_low_bu = df_subset.groupby('year')['anomaly'].mean().reset_index(); print(f"Aggregated LOW BU anomalies.")

ax.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1.02, 1), borderaxespad=0., fontsize=9, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white') # Place legend to the right

# --- Add Basemap Inlay ---
if basemap_available and df_meta_us_indexed is not None:
    print("Adding basemap inlay...")
    try:
        # Create inset axes using example coordinates adjusted slightly
        ax_inset = fig.add_axes([0.78, 0.15, 0.20, 0.20]) # Adjusted position slightly

        # Create Basemap instance for CONUS

        # Get coordinates and plot H8 stations

        if not h8_coords.empty: x, y = m(h8_coords[meta_lon_col].values, h8_coords[meta_lat_col].values); m.scatter(x, y, s=marker_size, color='cyan', marker='o', alpha=0.8, zorder=5, label='H8')

        # Get coordinates and plot Low BU stations
        low_bu_coords = df_meta_us_indexed.reindex(low_bu_stations_used_final).dropna(subset=[meta_lat_col, meta_lon_col])
        if not low_bu_coords.empty: x, y = m(low_bu_coords[meta_lon_col].values, low_bu_coords[meta_lat_col].values); m.scatter(x, y, s=marker_size, color='yellow', marker='x', alpha=0.8, zorder=6, label='Low BU')

# --- Function to Load and Process GHCN Data ---
# (Code remains the same)
def load_and_process_ghcn(data_url, file_suffix, needed_ids, s_year, e_year, m_months):
    print(f"\n--- Processing: {data_url.split('/')[-1]} ---")
    df_raw = pd.DataFrame(columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"]); dat_member_name="Unknown"
    try:
        print(f"Downloading data..."); response = requests.get(data_url, stream=True, timeout=60); response.raise_for_status(); tar_bytes = io.BytesIO(response.content)
        print(f"Extracting and filtering...")
        with tarfile.open(fileobj=tar_bytes, mode="r:gz") as tar:
            dat_members = [m for m in tar.getmembers() if m.name.endswith(file_suffix)];
            if not dat_members: raise ValueError(f"No {file_suffix} file in tar.")
            dat_member = dat_members[0]; dat_member_name = dat_member.name; print(f"Extracting from: {dat_member_name}")
            dat_file = tar.extractfile(dat_member); filtered_lines = []
            for line_bytes in dat_file:
                 try: line_str = line_bytes.decode("utf-8", errors='replace'); sid = line_str[0:11].strip()
                 except: continue
                 if sid in needed_ids and line_str[15:19] == "TAVG": filtered_lines.append(line_str)
        print(f"Found {len(filtered_lines)} relevant TAVG lines."); print(f"Parsing temperature data ({s_year}-{e_year})...")
        records = []
        for line in filtered_lines:
            try:
                sid = line[0:11].strip(); year = int(line[11:15])
                if year < s_year or year > e_year: continue
                monthly_temps = [np.nan]*12; valid_months = 0
                for m in range(12):
                    val_str = line[19 + m*8 : 24 + m*8].strip()
                    if val_str and val_str != "-9999": temp = int(val_str) / 100.0; monthly_temps[m]=temp; valid_months += 1
                if valid_months >= m_months:
                    yearly_avg = np.nanmean(monthly_temps)
                    if not np.isnan(yearly_avg): records.append([year, yearly_avg, sid])
            except: pass
        df_raw = pd.DataFrame(records, columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"])
        print(f"Parsed {len(df_raw)} valid yearly averages (min_months={m_months}).")
    except Exception as e: print(f"Data Loading/Processing Error: {e}")
    return df_raw, dat_member_name

# --- Function to Calculate Anomalies (RELAXED Coverage + RELAXED Baseline) ---
def calculate_anomalies(df_raw_data, series_station_ids, settings_dict):
    """Calculates anomalies using RELAXED coverage check (e.g., 90%) and RELAXED baseline check."""
    results = { 'anomalies': {}, 'stations_used': {}, 'counts': {} }
    baseline_s = settings_dict['baseline_start']; baseline_e = settings_dict['baseline_end']
    start_y = settings_dict['start_year']; end_y = settings_dict['end_year']
    orig_pairs = settings_dict['original_pairs']
    coverage_thresh = settings_dict['coverage_threshold_pct'] / 100.0 # Convert percentage to fraction

    # --- Series 1: H8 --- (Relaxed baseline)
    print(f"\nCalculating H8 USCRN Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_s}-{baseline_e})")
    h8_ids = series_station_ids['H8']; results['stations_used']['H8'] = list(h8_ids)
    original_pairwise_anomalies = []; df_raw_original = df_raw_data[df_raw_data['station_id'].isin(h8_ids)]
    h8_pairs_with_baseline_data = 0
    if not df_raw_original.empty:
        for legacy_id, uscrn_id in orig_pairs: # Pairwise loop logic unchanged
            df_legacy = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_uscrn = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_pair_tavg = pd.concat([df_legacy, df_uscrn], axis=1).mean(axis=1, skipna=True).reset_index()
            df_pair_tavg.columns = ["year", "tavg"]; df_pair_tavg = df_pair_tavg.dropna(subset=['tavg'])
            base_vals = df_pair_tavg[(df_pair_tavg["year"] >= baseline_s) & (df_pair_tavg["year"] <= baseline_e)]["tavg"]
            if base_vals.notna().any(): # Relaxed baseline check
                 baseline_mean = base_vals.mean()
                 df_pair_tavg["anomaly"] = df_pair_tavg["tavg"] - baseline_mean
                 original_pairwise_anomalies.append(df_pair_tavg[["year", "anomaly"]])
                 h8_pairs_with_baseline_data += 1
        if original_pairwise_anomalies:
            df_all_original = pd.concat(original_pairwise_anomalies); df_agg_original = df_all_original.groupby("year")["anomaly"].mean().reset_index()
            results['anomalies']['H8'] = df_agg_original; results['counts']['H8'] = h8_pairs_with_baseline_data
            print(f"Aggregated H8 USCRN from {h8_pairs_with_baseline_data} pairs with valid baseline data.")
    # Initialize if no results
    if 'H8' not in results['anomalies']: results['anomalies']['H8'] = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly'])
    if 'H8' not in results['counts']: results['counts']['H8'] = 0
    if 'H8' not in results['stations_used']: results['stations_used']['H8'] = list(h8_ids)

    # --- Series 2 & 3: BU --- (RELAXED coverage and RELAXED baseline)
    for series_name, bu_ids in [('LowBU', series_station_ids['LowBU']), ('HighBU', series_station_ids['HighBU'])]:
        print(f"\nCalculating {series_name} US Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_s}-{baseline_e})")
        df_raw_bu = df_raw_data[df_raw_data['station_id'].isin(bu_ids)];
        stations_meeting_relaxed_coverage = [] # Variable for clarity
        results['stations_used'][series_name] = []; results['counts'][series_name] = 0; results['anomalies'][series_name] = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly']) # Initialize
        if not df_raw_bu.empty:
            grouped = df_raw_bu.groupby('station_id'); total_years_in_range = end_y - start_y + 1
            min_years_required = int(total_years_in_range * coverage_thresh)

            # Step 1: Apply RELAXED coverage check
            for station_id, group in grouped:
                 if (group['year'].nunique() >= min_years_required and
                     group['year'].min() <= start_y + 10 and # Optional: keep rough start/end check
                     group['year'].max() >= end_y - 10):
                      stations_meeting_relaxed_coverage.append(station_id)

            print(f"Found {len(stations_meeting_relaxed_coverage)} {series_name} stations meeting RELAXED coverage criteria (>= {min_years_required} years).")
            if stations_meeting_relaxed_coverage:
                # Step 2: Apply RELAXED baseline check to the coverage-passing subset
                df_subset_coverage = df_raw_bu[df_raw_bu['station_id'].isin(stations_meeting_relaxed_coverage)].copy()
                baseline_data = df_subset_coverage[(df_subset_coverage['year'] >= baseline_s) & (df_subset_coverage['year'] <= baseline_e)]
                station_baselines_mean = baseline_data.groupby('station_id')['tavg'].mean()
                stations_with_baseline = station_baselines_mean.dropna().index # Select stations with a valid mean

                # Step 3: Determine FINAL list of stations used for plotting and N count
                final_stations_list = list(stations_with_baseline)
                final_station_count = len(final_stations_list)
                results['stations_used'][series_name] = final_stations_list; results['counts'][series_name] = final_station_count

                # Step 4: Calculate anomalies using ONLY the final list of stations
                if final_station_count > 0:
                    df_subset_final = df_subset_coverage[df_subset_coverage['station_id'].isin(final_stations_list)].copy()
                    print(f"Calculating {series_name} anomalies for {final_station_count} stations with valid baseline data.")
                    df_subset_final['baseline_mean'] = df_subset_final['station_id'].map(station_baselines_mean.dropna())
                    df_subset_final['anomaly'] = df_subset_final['tavg'] - df_subset_final['baseline_mean']
                    df_subset_final = df_subset_final.dropna(subset=['anomaly'])
                    df_agg_bu = df_subset_final.groupby('year')['anomaly'].mean().reset_index()
                    results['anomalies'][series_name] = df_agg_bu
                    print(f"Aggregated {series_name} anomalies.")
                # else: print(f"Warning: {len(stations_meeting_relaxed_coverage)} passed coverage, but none had valid baseline data. N=0.")
    return results

def plot_anomalies(anomaly_results, data_type_label, df_meta_idx, settings_dict, filename, common_ylim=None):
    """Generates the anomaly plot with basemap, using provided common Y limits."""

        min_lim = np.inf; max_lim = -np.inf
        if any_series_plotted:
             for s in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:

             if np.isfinite(min_lim) and np.isfinite(max_lim): ax.set_ylim(min_lim - 0.5, max_lim + 0.5)
             else: ax.set_ylim(-2.5, 3.5)

    fig.text(0.01, -0.03, f"Data: US Stations from GHCN v4 ({data_source_filename}) | Metadata: {meta_filename}\nYearly avg >= {settings['min_months']} months/yr | Baseline: {settings['baseline_start']}–{settings['baseline_end']} | Coverage: {settings['start_year']}-{settings['end_year']}\nH8: Avg({counts.get('H8', 0)} pairs) | LowBU: Avg(N={counts.get('LowBU', 0)}, {settings['low_bu_min']}-{settings['low_bu_max']}%) | HighBU: Avg(N={counts.get('HighBU', 0)}, >{settings['high_bu_min']}%)", fontsize=8.5, color='white', va='top')
    try: plt.savefig(filename, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='black'); print(f"Plot saved as {filename}")
    except Exception as e: print(f"\nError saving plot {filename}: {e}")
    plt.show(); plt.close(fig)


# --- Function to Plot Comparison (Static Only) ---
# (Code remains the same)
def plot_comparison(qcu_results, qcf_results, settings_dict, plot_filename):
    # ... (comparison plot code unchanged) ...
    print("\n--- Plotting QCU vs QCF LOESS Comparison (Static) ---")
    plt.style.use('dark_background'); fig_comp, ax_comp = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    qcu_anomalies = qcu_results['anomalies']; qcf_anomalies = qcf_results['anomalies']
    colors = settings_dict['plot_colors']; min_year_overall = settings_dict['start_year']; max_year_overall = settings_dict['end_year']
    min_anomaly_overall = np.inf; max_anomaly_overall = -np.inf; loess_data = {}; any_data = False
    for dt_label, anomalies_dict in [('QCU', qcu_anomalies), ('QCF', qcf_anomalies)]: # LOESS Calculation unchanged
        loess_data[dt_label] = {}
        for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
            df_agg = anomalies_dict.get(series_name)
            if df_agg is not None and not df_agg.empty and 'anomaly' in df_agg and df_agg['anomaly'].notna().any():
                 df_clean = df_agg.dropna(subset=['year', 'anomaly'])
                 if len(df_clean) > 5:
                     try: loess = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["anomaly"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings_dict['smoothing_frac'])
                     except Exception as e: print(f"LOESS Error ({dt_label}-{series_name}): {e}"); continue
                     if loess.ndim == 2 and loess.shape[1] == 2: loess_data[dt_label][series_name] = {'years': loess[:, 0], 'anomalies': loess[:, 1]}; min_anomaly_overall = min(min_anomaly_overall, loess[:, 1].min()); max_anomaly_overall = max(max_anomaly_overall, loess[:, 1].max()); any_data = True
    if not any_data: print("No LOESS data for comparison."); plt.close(fig_comp); return
    if np.isfinite(min_anomaly_overall) and np.isfinite(max_anomaly_overall): min_anomaly_overall -= 0.2; max_anomaly_overall += 0.2
    else: min_anomaly_overall = -2.0; max_anomaly_overall = 3.0
    plot_lines = []; plot_labels = [] # Plotting loop unchanged
    for dt_label, line_style, lw in [('QCU', settings_dict['qcu_linestyle'], settings_dict['qcu_linewidth_smooth']), ('QCF', settings_dict['qcf_linestyle'], settings_dict['qcf_linewidth_smooth'])]:
        for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
             if loess_data.get(dt_label, {}).get(series_name): data = loess_data[dt_label][series_name]; line, = ax_comp.plot(data['years'], data['anomalies'], color=colors[series_name], linestyle=line_style, linewidth=lw, alpha=0.9); label = f"{series_name} ({dt_label})"; plot_lines.append(line); plot_labels.append(label)
    # Axis setup unchanged...
    ax_comp.set_title(f"Comparison of LOESS Smoothed US Anomalies (QCU vs QCF)", fontsize=14, weight='bold', color='white')
    ax_comp.set_xlabel("Year", fontsize=12, color='white'); ax_comp.set_ylabel("Smoothed Temperature Anomaly (°C)", fontsize=12, color='white')
    ax_comp.tick_params(axis='x', colors='white'); ax_comp.tick_params(axis='y', colors='white'); ax_comp.set_xlim(min_year_overall, max_year_overall); ax_comp.set_ylim(min_anomaly_overall, max_anomaly_overall)
    ax_comp.grid(True, alpha=0.3, color='gray'); ax_comp.axhline(0, color='white', linestyle=':', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.5)
    if plot_lines: ax_comp.legend(plot_lines, plot_labels, loc='upper left', fontsize=9, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white', ncol=2)
    # Footnotes unchanged...
    meta_filename = metadata_url.split('/')[-1]; fig_comp.text(0.01, -0.03, f"Data: GHCN v4 QCU & QCF | Metadata: {meta_filename}\nSmoothed anomaly comparison | LOESS frac={settings_dict['smoothing_frac']} | Baseline: {settings_dict['baseline_start']}–{settings_dict['baseline_end']}\nCoverage: {settings_dict['start_year']}-{settings_dict['end_year']} | Derived from stations meeting criteria in individual plots.", fontsize=8.5, color='white', va='top')
    try: fig_comp.savefig(plot_filename, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='black'); print(f"Comparison plot saved as {plot_filename}")
    except Exception as e: print(f"\nError saving comparison plot {plot_filename}: {e}")
    plt.show(); plt.close(fig_comp)


# --- Function to Plot Difference (using RAW temps) ---
# (Code remains the same)
def plot_difference(df_raw_qcu, df_raw_qcf, qcu_results, qcf_results, settings_dict, plot_filename):
    # ... (difference plot code unchanged) ...
    print("\n--- Plotting QCF - QCU Adjustment (Smoothed Raw Temperature Difference) ---")
    plt.style.use('dark_background'); fig_diff, ax_diff = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    colors = settings_dict['plot_colors']; min_year_overall = settings_dict['start_year']; max_year_overall = settings_dict['end_year']
    min_diff_overall = np.inf; max_diff_overall = -np.inf; loess_diff_data = {}; any_diff_data = False; common_station_counts = {}
    # --- BU Series --- (Logic unchanged)
    for series_name in ['LowBU', 'HighBU']:
        print(f"Processing raw difference for {series_name} using common stations...")
        stations_qcu = set(qcu_results['stations_used'].get(series_name, [])); stations_qcf = set(qcf_results['stations_used'].get(series_name, []))
        common_stations = list(stations_qcu.intersection(stations_qcf)); common_station_counts[series_name] = len(common_stations)
        print(f"  Found {len(common_stations)} common stations for {series_name}.")
        if not common_stations or df_raw_qcu is None or df_raw_qcf is None: print(f"  Skipping {series_name} difference."); loess_diff_data[series_name] = None; continue
        df_common_qcu_raw = df_raw_qcu[df_raw_qcu['station_id'].isin(common_stations)].copy(); df_common_qcf_raw = df_raw_qcf[df_raw_qcf['station_id'].isin(common_stations)].copy()
        df_avg_raw_qcu = df_common_qcu_raw.groupby('year')['tavg'].mean().reset_index(); df_avg_raw_qcf = df_common_qcf_raw.groupby('year')['tavg'].mean().reset_index()
        df_merged_raw = pd.merge(df_avg_raw_qcf, df_avg_raw_qcu, on='year', suffixes=('_qcf', '_qcu'), how='inner')
        if not df_merged_raw.empty:
            df_merged_raw['difference'] = df_merged_raw['tavg_qcf'] - df_merged_raw['tavg_qcu']
            df_clean = df_merged_raw.dropna(subset=['year', 'difference'])
            if len(df_clean) > 5:
                try: loess_diff = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["difference"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings_dict['smoothing_frac'])
                except Exception as e: print(f"  LOESS Error ({series_name} raw diff): {e}"); continue
                if loess_diff.ndim == 2 and loess_diff.shape[1] == 2: loess_diff_data[series_name] = {'years': loess_diff[:, 0], 'difference': loess_diff[:, 1]}; min_diff_overall = min(min_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].min()); max_diff_overall = max(max_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].max()); any_diff_data = True
    # --- H8 Series --- (Logic unchanged)
    print(f"Processing raw difference for H8 using pairwise averages...")
    series_name = 'H8'; pairwise_raw_diffs = []; pairs_used_count = 0
    if df_raw_qcu is not None and df_raw_qcf is not None:
        df_raw_qcu_h8 = df_raw_qcu[df_raw_qcu['station_id'].isin(station_id_groups['H8'])]; df_raw_qcf_h8 = df_raw_qcf[df_raw_qcf['station_id'].isin(station_id_groups['H8'])]
        for legacy_id, uscrn_id in settings_dict['original_pairs']:
            df_legacy_qcu = df_raw_qcu_h8[df_raw_qcu_h8["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]; df_uscrn_qcu = df_raw_qcu_h8[df_raw_qcu_h8["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_pair_tavg_qcu = pd.concat([df_legacy_qcu, df_uscrn_qcu], axis=1).mean(axis=1, skipna=True)
            df_legacy_qcf = df_raw_qcf_h8[df_raw_qcf_h8["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]; df_uscrn_qcf = df_raw_qcf_h8[df_raw_qcf_h8["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_pair_tavg_qcf = pd.concat([df_legacy_qcf, df_uscrn_qcf], axis=1).mean(axis=1, skipna=True)
            df_pair_diff = (df_pair_tavg_qcf - df_pair_tavg_qcu).dropna().reset_index(); df_pair_diff.columns = ['year', 'difference']
            if not df_pair_diff.empty: pairwise_raw_diffs.append(df_pair_diff); pairs_used_count += 1
        if pairwise_raw_diffs:
            df_all_h8_diff = pd.concat(pairwise_raw_diffs); df_agg_h8_diff = df_all_h8_diff.groupby("year")["difference"].mean().reset_index()
            df_clean = df_agg_h8_diff.dropna(subset=['year', 'difference'])
            if len(df_clean) > 5:
                 try: loess_diff = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["difference"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings_dict['smoothing_frac'])
                 except Exception as e: print(f"  LOESS Error (H8 raw diff): {e}")
                 else:
                      if loess_diff.ndim == 2 and loess_diff.shape[1] == 2: loess_diff_data[series_name] = {'years': loess_diff[:, 0], 'difference': loess_diff[:, 1]}; min_diff_overall = min(min_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].min()); max_diff_overall = max(max_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].max()); any_diff_data = True
            print(f"  Aggregated H8 raw difference from {pairs_used_count} pairs.")
    # --- Plotting --- (Logic unchanged)
    if not any_diff_data: print("No difference LOESS data available to plot."); plt.close(fig_diff); return
    if np.isfinite(min_diff_overall) and np.isfinite(max_diff_overall): lim_range = max(0.2, max_diff_overall - min_diff_overall); y_lower = min_diff_overall - lim_range * 0.1; y_upper = max_diff_overall + lim_range * 0.1; y_lower = min(y_lower, -0.05); y_upper = max(y_upper, 0.05)
    else: y_lower, y_upper = -1.0, 1.0
    plot_lines = []; plot_labels = []
    for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
        if loess_diff_data.get(series_name):
            data = loess_diff_data[series_name]; label = f"{series_name} Raw Adjustment (QCF-QCU)"
            if series_name in common_station_counts: label += f" (N={common_station_counts[series_name]})"
            elif series_name == 'H8': label += f" (Avg {pairs_used_count} Pairs)"
            line, = ax_diff.plot(data['years'], data['difference'], color=colors[series_name], linestyle='-', linewidth=settings_dict['qcu_linewidth_smooth'], alpha=0.9)
            plot_lines.append(line); plot_labels.append(label)
    # Axis setup unchanged...
    ax_diff.set_title(f"Smoothed GHCN Raw Temp Adjustment (QCF - QCU)", fontsize=14, weight='bold', color='white')
    ax_diff.set_xlabel("Year", fontsize=12, color='white'); ax_diff.set_ylabel("Avg Temp Difference (°C)", fontsize=12, color='white')
    ax_diff.tick_params(axis='x', colors='white'); ax_diff.tick_params(axis='y', colors='white')
    ax_diff.set_xlim(min_year_overall, max_year_overall); ax_diff.set_ylim(y_lower, y_upper)
    ax_diff.grid(True, alpha=0.3, color='gray'); ax_diff.axhline(0, color='white', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.0, alpha=0.7)
    if plot_lines: ax_diff.legend(plot_lines, plot_labels, loc='best', fontsize=9, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white')
    # Footnotes unchanged...
    fig_diff.text(0.01, -0.04, f"Data: GHCN v4 QCF - QCU | LOESS frac={settings_dict['smoothing_frac']}\nPlot shows smoothed difference between QCF and QCU *raw yearly average temperatures*.\nLowBU/HighBU based on stations common to both QCU/QCF filtered results (N in legend).\nH8 based on average of pairwise QCF-QCU raw temperature differences.", fontsize=8.5, color='white', va='top')
    try: fig_diff.savefig(plot_filename, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='black'); print(f"Difference plot saved as {plot_filename}")
    except Exception as e: print(f"\nError saving difference plot {plot_filename}: {e}")
    plt.show(); plt.close(fig_diff)


# === Helper Function for Plotting Content on Existing Axes ===
# (Code remains the same)
def _plot_anomaly_content(ax, anomaly_results, data_type_label, settings_dict, common_ylim):
    """Plots anomaly data onto a provided Axes object."""
    counts = anomaly_results['counts']; anomalies = anomaly_results['anomalies']
    colors = settings_dict['plot_colors']; markers = settings_dict['plot_markers']
    linewidth_raw = settings_dict[f"{data_type_label.lower()}_linewidth_raw"]; linewidth_smooth = settings_dict[f"{data_type_label.lower()}_linewidth_smooth"]
    ax.axhline(0, color='white', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.5)
    plot_lines = []
    plot_labels = []
    for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
        df_agg = anomalies.get(series_name); count = counts.get(series_name, 0)
        if df_agg is not None and not df_agg.empty and count > 0:
            try:
                series_label_base = f"{series_name}"; series_label_count = f"N={count}"
                if series_name == 'LowBU': series_label_base = f"Low BU ({settings_dict['low_bu_min']}-{settings_dict['low_bu_max']}%)"
                if series_name == 'HighBU': series_label_base = f"High BU (>{settings_dict['high_bu_min']}%)"
                if series_name == 'H8': series_label_count = f"N={count} pairs"
                df_clean = df_agg.dropna(subset=['year', 'anomaly'])
                if len(df_clean) > 5:
                    loess = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["anomaly"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings_dict['smoothing_frac'])
                    if loess.ndim == 2 and loess.shape[1] == 2:
                         line_loess, = ax.plot(loess[:, 0], loess[:, 1], color=colors[series_name], linewidth=linewidth_smooth, alpha=0.9)
                         plot_lines.append(line_loess); plot_labels.append(f"{series_label_base} LOESS")
                line_raw, = ax.plot(df_agg["year"], df_agg["anomaly"], color=colors[series_name], linewidth=linewidth_raw, marker=markers[series_name], markersize=3, alpha=0.7, linestyle='-' if linewidth_raw > 0 else 'None')
                plot_lines.append(line_raw); plot_labels.append(f"{series_label_base} Anomaly ({series_label_count})")
            except Exception as e: print(f"Subplot Anomaly Error ({data_type_label} - {series_name}): {e}")
    ax.set_ylabel("Anomaly (°C)", color='white') # Ensure label color
    if common_ylim: ax.set_ylim(common_ylim)
    ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3); ax.tick_params(axis='y', colors='white')
    if plot_lines: ax.legend(plot_lines, plot_labels, loc='upper left', fontsize=8, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white')
    ax.set_facecolor('black') # Ensure background

def _plot_difference_content(ax, loess_diff_data, common_station_counts, pairs_used_count, settings_dict):
    """Plots difference data onto a provided Axes object."""
    colors = settings_dict['plot_colors'];
    min_diff_overall = np.inf; max_diff_overall = -np.inf; any_diff_data = False
    plot_lines = []
    plot_labels = []
    for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
        if loess_diff_data.get(series_name):
            data = loess_diff_data[series_name]
            min_diff_overall = min(min_diff_overall, data['difference'].min()); max_diff_overall = max(max_diff_overall, data['difference'].max()); any_diff_data = True
            label = f"{series_name} Raw Adj."
            if series_name in common_station_counts: label += f" (N={common_station_counts[series_name]})"
            elif series_name == 'H8': label += f" (Avg {pairs_used_count} Pairs)"
            line, = ax.plot(data['years'], data['difference'], color=colors[series_name], linestyle='-', linewidth=settings_dict['qcu_linewidth_smooth'], alpha=0.9)
            plot_lines.append(line); plot_labels.append(label)
    if not any_diff_data: return
    if np.isfinite(min_diff_overall) and np.isfinite(max_diff_overall):
        lim_range = max(0.2, max_diff_overall - min_diff_overall); y_lower = min_diff_overall - lim_range * 0.1; y_upper = max_diff_overall + lim_range * 0.1; y_lower = min(y_lower, -0.05); y_upper = max(y_upper, 0.05)
    else: y_lower, y_upper = -1.0, 1.0
    ax.set_ylim(y_lower, y_upper)
    ax.axhline(0, color='white', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.0, alpha=0.7)
    ax.set_ylabel("Adjustment (°C)", color='white') # Ensure label color
    ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3); ax.tick_params(axis='y', colors='white')
    if plot_lines: ax.legend(plot_lines, plot_labels, loc='best', fontsize=8, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white')
    ax.set_facecolor('black') # Ensure background

    series_name = 'H8'; pairwise_raw_diffs = []
    df_raw_qcu_h8 = raw_data_frames["QCU"][raw_data_frames["QCU"]['station_id'].isin(station_id_groups['H8'])]; df_raw_qcf_h8 = raw_data_frames["QCF"][raw_data_frames["QCF"]['station_id'].isin(station_id_groups['H8'])]
    for legacy_id, uscrn_id in settings['original_pairs']:
        df_l_qcu=df_raw_qcu_h8[df_raw_qcu_h8["station_id"]==legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]; df_u_qcu=df_raw_qcu_h8[df_raw_qcu_h8["station_id"]==uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
        df_p_qcu=pd.concat([df_l_qcu, df_u_qcu], axis=1).mean(axis=1, skipna=True)
        df_l_qcf=df_raw_qcf_h8[df_raw_qcf_h8["station_id"]==legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]; df_u_qcf=df_raw_qcf_h8[df_raw_qcf_h8["station_id"]==uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
        df_p_qcf=pd.concat([df_l_qcf, df_u_qcf], axis=1).mean(axis=1, skipna=True)
        df_p_diff=(df_p_qcf - df_p_qcu).dropna().reset_index(); df_p_diff.columns=['year','difference']
        if not df_p_diff.empty: pairwise_raw_diffs.append(df_p_diff); h8_pairs_count_for_combined += 1
    if pairwise_raw_diffs:
        df_all_h8=pd.concat(pairwise_raw_diffs); df_agg_h8=df_all_h8.groupby("year")["difference"].mean().reset_index(); df_clean = df_agg_h8.dropna(subset=['year', 'difference'])
        if len(df_clean) > 5:
            try: loess_diff = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["difference"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings['smoothing_frac'])
            except Exception as e: print(f"Combined Plot LOESS Error (H8 raw diff): {e}")
            else:
                if loess_diff.ndim == 2 and loess_diff.shape[1] == 2: diff_loess_data_for_combined[series_name] = {'years': loess_diff[:, 0], 'difference': loess_diff[:, 1]}; min_diff_overall = min(min_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].min()); max_diff_overall = max(max_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].max()); any_diff_data_for_combined = True
    # Call the standalone difference plot
    plot_difference( raw_data_frames["QCU"], raw_data_frames["QCF"], processed_data["QCU"], processed_data["QCF"], settings, plot4_filename )
    # --- Generate Combined Plots ---
    print("\n--- Generating Combined Plots ---")
    combined_png_a = os.path.join(output_dir, "combined_qcu_difference.png")
    combined_png_b = os.path.join(output_dir, "combined_qcf_difference.png")
    # Plot A: QCU + Difference
    if plot1_exists and any_diff_data_for_combined: # Check dependencies
        fig_a, axs_a = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(10, 10), sharex=True, facecolor='black')
        plt.style.use('dark_background')
        _plot_anomaly_content(axs_a[0], processed_data["QCU"], "QCU", settings, common_anomaly_ylim)
        axs_a[0].set_title(f"QCU Anomalies (Baseline {settings['baseline_start']}–{settings['baseline_end']})", color='white')
        _plot_difference_content(axs_a[1], diff_loess_data_for_combined, common_stn_counts_for_combined, h8_pairs_count_for_combined, settings)
        axs_a[1].set_title("Smoothed Raw Temp Adjustment (QCF - QCU)", color='white')
        axs_a[1].set_xlabel("Year"); axs_a[0].tick_params(labelbottom=False) # Hide x labels on top plot
        fig_a.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.01, 1, 0.97], h_pad=2.0) # Adjust layout & padding
        fig_a.suptitle("GHCNv4 US Temperature: QCU Anomalies and QCF-QCU Adjustment", color='white', y=0.99)
        try: fig_a.savefig(combined_png_a, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='black'); print(f"Combined plot A saved as {combined_png_a}")
        except Exception as e: print(f"Error saving combined plot A: {e}")
        plt.close(fig_a)
    else: combined_png_a = None
    # Plot B: QCF + Difference
    if plot2_exists and any_diff_data_for_combined: # Check dependencies
        fig_b, axs_b = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(10, 10), sharex=True, facecolor='black')
        plt.style.use('dark_background')
        _plot_anomaly_content(axs_b[0], processed_data["QCF"], "QCF", settings, common_anomaly_ylim)
        axs_b[0].set_title(f"QCF Anomalies (Baseline {settings['baseline_start']}–{settings['baseline_end']})", color='white')
        _plot_difference_content(axs_b[1], diff_loess_data_for_combined, common_stn_counts_for_combined, h8_pairs_count_for_combined, settings)
        axs_b[1].set_title("Smoothed Raw Temp Adjustment (QCF - QCU)", color='white')
        axs_b[1].set_xlabel("Year"); axs_b[0].tick_params(labelbottom=False) # Hide x labels on top plot
        fig_b.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.01, 1, 0.97], h_pad=2.0) # Adjust layout & padding
        fig_b.suptitle("GHCNv4 US Temperature: QCF Anomalies and QCF-QCU Adjustment", color='white', y=0.99)
        try: fig_b.savefig(combined_png_b, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='black'); print(f"Combined plot B saved as {combined_png_b}")
        except Exception as e: print(f"Error saving combined plot B: {e}")
        plt.close(fig_b)
    else: combined_png_b = None
    # --- Generate Animated GIF ---
    if combined_png_a and combined_png_b: # Check if both PNGs were created
        print("\n--- Generating Animated GIF ---")
        gif_filename = os.path.join(output_dir, "animated_qcu_qcf_vs_difference.gif")
        try:
            with imageio.get_writer(gif_filename, mode='I', duration=gif_frame_delay, loop=0) as writer:
                writer.append_data(imageio.imread(combined_png_a))
                writer.append_data(imageio.imread(combined_png_b))
            print(f"Animated GIF saved as {gif_filename}")
        except FileNotFoundError: print(f"Error creating GIF: Could not read input PNG files.")
        except Exception as e: print(f"Error creating GIF: {e}")
    else: print("\nSkipping GIF creation: One or both combined PNGs are missing.")
else: print("\nSkipping comparison, difference, combined plots and GIF: Missing base QCU or QCF results.")

--- Summary of Observations ---
The analysis compares raw (QCU) and homogenized (QCF) GHCNv4 temperature data for different US station groups:
1. H8: 8 specific USCRN/Historical pairs.
2. LowBU: Stations with low surrounding built-up land percentage (0.1-2.0%).
3. HighBU: Stations with high surrounding built-up land percentage (>10%).

Based on the generated plots:
- Plot 1 (QCU) shows raw temperature anomalies.
- Plot 2 (QCF) shows homogenized temperature anomalies (using the same baseline).
- Plot 3 compares the smoothed trends of QCU vs. QCF anomalies.
- Plot 4 shows the smoothed *adjustment* (difference between QCF and QCU raw temperatures).

Interpretation:
Observing Plot 4 (QCF-QCU Adjustment), note the difference in adjustments applied over time:
 - The LowBU (yellow line) stations often show a net cooling adjustment in earlier decades (difference is negative), while showing less adjustment or slight warming recently.
 - The HighBU (red line, typically urban/town) stations show smaller adjustments overall, particularly less cooling in the past compared to LowBU.
This pattern, where rural/LowBU stations are adjusted downwards (cooled) in the past more significantly than urban/HighBU stations, could suggest that the Pairwise Homogenization Algorithm (PHA) might be overcorrecting for potential historical data issues or introducing a cooling bias in less urbanized records.
